        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Maximizing Resource Efficiency</div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <p>Clear documentation of leases allows for better planning, resource allocation, and the avoidance of overlaps in land usage. This maximizes productivity and minimizes operational inefficiencies.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Legal Aspects of Lease Management Section -->
    <section class="section-bg">
        <h2>What Legal Aspects Need to Be Taken into Account When Managing Agricultural Leases?</h2>
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Key Legal Considerations</div>
            <div class="card-content">
                <p>When managing agricultural leases, it is essential to consider the following legal aspects:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Contract Terms:</strong> Clearly define lease duration, payment terms, and land usage.</li>
                    <li><strong>Notice Period:</strong> Agree on a clear notice period for contract termination or renewal.</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Compliance:</strong> Ensure that all agreements comply with local regulations on land use, taxation, and environmental protection.</li>
                    <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Careful documentation of contracts, amendments, and notices is crucial to protect both parties legally.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
